 patient, where a fingerprint of the cornea is taken, then the information is transferred to the laser vision correction device to apply laser strikes to specific places on the surface of the cornea in order to modify the shape of the cornea and reach the ideal shape Which gives the best acuity of eyesight.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt .5in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&middot;<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>A device for measuring the number and shape of corneal lining cells (specular microscope)</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt .5in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&middot;<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>It is the newest and most accurate device of its kind in the region, which is used before cataract operations to determine the ability of the cornea to withstand the operation, thus preventing weakness in the cornea after the cataract operation and the need for corneal transplantation, in addition to using the device in following up cases after corneal transplantation operations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt .5in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&middot;<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Optical Coherence Tomography device - OTC: It is a non-invasive imaging technology used to obtain high-resolution cross-sectional images of the retina.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt .5in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&middot