 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: #333333; font-family: Cairo, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out 0s; color: #333333; font-family: Cairo, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2021-01-03 09:29:53','2021-01-03 09:29:53'),(1704,'objectives','title',6,'en','We aspire to support and encourage young talents, highlighting local artists, immortalizing their works, integrating art with therapy and society, in addition to raising the artistic taste of society by visually satisfying them with paintings and pictures of high quality and artistic value.','2021-01-03 09:30:33','2021-01-03 09:30:33'),(1705,'objectives','title',7,'en','More than 2000 works were received, including painting, photography, sculpture, and calligraphy, from which we selected 200 works. In addition, awards were given to artists, with a total amount of 400,000 Saudi riyals.','2021-01-03 09:31:13','2021-01-03 09:31:13'),(1706,'community_contents','title',16,'en','\"Al-Ahsaa\" Run Race','2021-01-03 09:35:31','2021-01-03 09:35:31'),(1707,'community_contents','content',16,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Under the auspices of Al-Mousa Specialist Hospital - General Sports Authority - Saudi Federation for Community Sports.</span></p>','2021-01-03 09:35:31','2021-01-03 09:35:31'),(1708,'community_contents','title',17,'en','About \"Al-Ahsaa\" Run Race','2021-01-03 09:38:26','2021-01-03 09:38:26'),(1709,'community_contents','content',17,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&ldquo;Al-Ahsaa Run&rdquo; is an annual race organized by Al-Moosa Specialist Hospital in cooperation with the Public Authority for Sports, which aims to increase awareness of the importance of running and a healthy lifestyle.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Sport is the most important method adopted to prevent diseases, as it reduces the deposition of fats inside the blood vessels, and increases energy consumption inside the body, which leads to burning bad fats and reducing the risk of heart disease and strokes.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The race is highly popular, with more than 8,000 participants, including adults, children, elderly people, people with special needs, and women. Prizes vary between cars, material sums, and valuable prizes offered to the winners.</span></p>','2021-01-03 09:38:26','2021-01-03 09:38:26'),(1710,'community_contents','title',18,'en','Treating a Cleft Lip','2021-01-03 09:41:25','2021-01-03 09:41:25'),(1711,'community_contents','content',18,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0in; text-align: center;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Under the auspices of Al-Moosa Specialist Hospital and Al-Ber Charity Society</span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0in; text-align: center;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Cleft lip deformity is one of the deformities that cause very bad psychological effects on the child and his family, which may sometimes lead to the child entering severe depressive episodes due to ridicule of him by his colleagues in school or the street, which makes the child live a miserable childhood.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The process of repairing a cleft lip is not covered by insurance, and the waiting period may be prolonged in government hospitals. From here came the idea of ​​treating children with this deformity, to draw a smile of hope on their lips, and from here came I thought of calling the program \"<strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">a smile of hope.\"</strong></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>','2021-01-03 09:41:25','2021-01-04 12:08:39'),(1712,'community_contents','title',19,'en','\"We Play Together\" Garden','2021-01-03 09:46:27','2021-01-03 09:46:27'),(1713,'community_contents','content',19,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>We believe, in Al-Moosa Specialist Hospital in the societal role of organizations and the extent of its success and effectiveness. We also believe in the right of all members of society to receive an equal amount of service, care, and entertainment as well.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Therefore, the idea of ​​&ldquo;We Play Together&rdquo; gardens, which is considered one of the initiatives of Al Muhaidib for community service, was the cooperation between Al Moosa Hospital And Al-Muhaidib Company to establish the first merging garden for children with special needs with their healthy peers, to be the product of a distinguished community partnership between Al-Muhaidib for Community Service and Al-Moosa Specialist Hospital.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\">&nbsp;</p>','2021-01-03 09:46:27','2021-01-04 12:15:37'),(1714,'community_contents','title',20,'en','Initiative: A Paramedic in Every School \"Everyone is a Paramedic\"','2021-01-03 09:49:52','2021-01-03 09:49:52'),(1715,'community_contents','content',20,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Under the auspices of the Life Support Center of El-Moosa Specialist Hospital - Education Department</span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&nbsp;</span></p>','2021-01-03 09:49:52','2021-01-04 12:22:56'),(1719,'doctors','slug',160,'en','dr-ahmed-ali-ghawas','2021-01-03 10:10:48','2021-01-03 10:10:48'),(1720,'doctors','name',160,'en','Dr. Ahmed Ali Ghawas','2021-01-03 10:10:48','2021-01-03 10:10:48'),(1721,'doctors','title',160,'en','Internal medicine doctor','2021-01-03 10:10:48','2021-01-03 10:10:48'),(1722,'doctors','qualifications',160,'en','Specialty: Internal Medicine Physician\nDegree:	-\nAreas of Expertise: -\nLanguages:	-\nNationality: -\nAge group of patients: -\n','2021-01-03 10:10:48','2021-01-03 10:10:48'),(1723,'doctors','slug',161,'en','dr-batal-al-dossary','2021-01-03 10:12:21','2021-01-03 10:12:21'),(1724,'doctors','name',161,'en','Dr. Batal Al-Dossary','2021-01-03 10:12:21','2021-01-03 10:12:21'),(1725,'doctors','title',161,'en','Thoracic consultant and head of the internal medicine department','2021-01-03 10:12:21','2021-01-03 10:12:21'),(1726,'doctors','qualifications',161,'en','Specialty: Consultant chest and head of internal medicine\nDegree: Holder of the American Board of Pulmonary Medicine, Fellowship of the American College of Chest Physicians, FCCP, Fellowship of the Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons of Canada, FRCP\nAreas of Expertise: Has more than 34 years of experience in the field of treating chest diseases\nLanguages: Arabic - English\nNationality: Saudi\nAge group of patients: adults\n','2021-01-03 10:12:21','2021-01-03 10:12:21'),(1727,'doctors','current_positions',161,'en','head of the internal medicine department','2021-01-03 10:12:21','2021-01-03 10:12:21'),(1728,'blogs','title',9,'en','Premenstrual Syndrome (PMS)‏','2021-01-03 10:13:56','2021-01-03 10:13:56'),(1729,'blogs','slug',9,'en','premenstrual-syndrome-pms','2021-01-03 10:13:56','2021-01-03 10:13:56'),(1730,'blogs','content',9,'en','<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Ambiguity surrounds the changes that occur to the female before menstruation and the menstrual CYCLE, unfortunately there are lot of misconceptions around that topic, in this article we will try to cover a phenomenon that every female should know and be aware of. Premenstrual syndrome, a term refers to a group of symptoms that afflict a woman about one to two weeks before menstruation (period), and these symptoms vary between physical, psychological and emotional, and these symptoms usually subside and disappear after the menstrual bleeding. Researchers have not been able to uncover the mystery surrounding the causes of premenstrual syndrome, so the most common explanation at the present time suggests that these symptoms come as a result of periodic changes in:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-29314 size-medium\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Female hormones</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Pituitary hormones</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Prostaglandins</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Certain chemicals in the brain (neurotransmitters)</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>From another perspective that should not be overlooked, the lifestyle followed may play a role in the emergence of premenstrual syndrome. It has been found that certain symptoms affect mostly women who:</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Smokes</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Live a life filled with tension and stress</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">rarely exercise</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Not getting enough sleep</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Or those who follow a diet rich in:</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Caffeine</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">salt</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Red meat</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Sugar</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Despite this, the nature of the association of these factors and life habits with premenstrual syndrome is still mysterious, and we still do not know for sure which of it is the definite cause , so is stress and tension, for example, the cause of this annoying syndrome? Or is it the result of it? In any case, what is more likely &ndash; until now &ndash; that premenstrual syndrome usually causes stress and tension and not the other way around. It seems that some drugs may relate as well, as we find that the contraceptive pill causes symptoms of premenstrual syndrome in some women, and we see them lead to symptoms improvement or in others.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">The medical community debates about the difference between premenstrual dysfunction and actual premenstrual syndrome, as most women of menstruation (about 75% of them) share those uncomfortable pre-menstrual symptoms. Despite this large number, one in ten women has symptoms severe enough to the point of disrupting their personal and social relationships, hindering their work, or performing their household tasks. Some doctors consider these severe symptoms to be what should be called premenstrual syndrome. On the other hand, another group of doctors disagrees with this opinion. There is a more severe form of premenstrual syndrome called premenstrual dysphoric disorder (PMDD). A woman is diagnosed with this disorder when she suffers from 5 or more symptoms of premenstrual syndrome, and usually shows mood swings, anger, irritability, anxiety and tension.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Premenstrual syndrome symptoms are divided into two main parts:</span></p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Physical symptoms:</strong></span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-29308 size-medium\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Bloating</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Breast tenderness (i.e. increased sensitivity to pain)</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Swollen feet and ankles</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Fluid retention and weight gain</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Painful uterine contractions before and during the first few days of menstruation</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Headache</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Cravings for food (especially salty or sweet food)</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">acne</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Decreased energy or fatigue</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Palpitations</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Dizziness</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Back pain or muscle pain</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Psychological and emotional symptoms:</strong></span></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Stress</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Mood Swings</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Depression</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Aggressiveness</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Crying spells</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Difficulty concentrating</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Forgetting some incidents</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Changes in sexual desire</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Symptoms of premenstrual syndrome differ from one woman to another, but in most women there are three complaints that top the list: moodiness, fatigue and bloating.</span></p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Diagnosis:</strong></span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">The doctor usually asks about the following:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-29316 size-medium\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Your premenstrual syndrome symptoms</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">When these symptoms appear in relation to your usual menstrual cycle</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Symptom regularity (coming monthly, biweekly, etc.)</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Your doctor will also ask you about your general life. Questions might include:</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Have you been feeling sad, or anxious lately?</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Do you notice mood swings? Or stress? Or difficulty concentrating?</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Are you experiencing difficulties with your spouse, family members, or co-workers?</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Are you in such a hurry that it disturbs your sleep and makes you skip meals?</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Are you living a sedentary lifestyle and not getting enough exercise?</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Do you smoke cigarettes?</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Is your diet high in red meat, salty food, or sugars?</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">After that, your doctor will review your medical history, ask you about any medications you are currently taking, then examine you and, if necessary, perform an examination using a Pap smear. No single physical symptom can confirm a diagnosis of premenstrual syndrome, but a comprehensive examination can help reveal other medical problems, such as hypothyroidism or a tumor in the breast, brain or ovary. This also applies to laboratory tests, there is no single laboratory test that can confirm your diagnosis of PMS, but blood tests help rule out other medical disorders, such as low blood sugar, hypothyroidism, or other hormonal problems that may be present. A cause for your symptoms.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">If your previous test results look normal, your doctor may ask you to keep a daily record of your menstrual symptoms for two or three months to write:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Symptom type</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Symptom severity</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Timing of your period</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Any stress that affected your life during that period. Your doctor will review the record you wrote to see if symptoms appear in a pattern that matches your premenstrual syndrome. Definitely, it cannot be said that the diagnosed condition is premenstrual syndrome if symptoms have not disappeared for about two weeks during the menstrual cycle, as symptoms usually disappear shortly after the start of menstruation until the next ovulation.</span></p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>How long would it last?</strong></span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Premenstrual syndrome may be a long-term condition for some women, as they experience the aforementioned symptoms beforehand</span></p>','2021-01-03 10:13:56','2021-01-03 10:13:56'),(1731,'doctors','slug',162,'en','dr-mustafa-saad','2021-01-03 10:14:40','2021-01-03 10:14:40'),(1732,'doctors','name',162,'en','Dr. Mustafa Saad','2021-01-03 10:14:40','2021-01-03 10:14:40'),(1733,'doctors','title',162,'en','Internal Medicine Consultant and Head of the Infectious Diseases and Immunology Department','2021-01-03 10:14:40','2021-01-03 10:14:40'),(1734,'doctors','qualifications',162,'en','Specialty: Consultant Internal Medicine and Head of the Infectious Diseases and Immunology Department\nDegree: Doctor of Internal Medicine and Infectious Diseases\nAreas of Expertise: Internal Medicine (Infectious Diseases and Immunology)\nLanguages: Arabic and English\nNationality: Jordanian\nAge group of patients: adults and children\n','2021-01-03 10:14:40','2021-01-03 10:14:40'),(1735,'doctors','current_positions',162,'en','Head of the Infectious Diseases and Immunology Department','2021-01-03 10:14:40','2021-01-03 10:14:40'),(1736,'blogs','title',10,'en','SAVING THE LIFE OF A 29-YEAR-OLD MAN HIS STOMACH MOVED AND SETTLED IN HIS CHEST FOR 7 YEARS','2021-01-03 10:28:57','2021-01-03 10:28:57'),(1737,'blogs','slug',10,'en','saving-the-life-of-a-29-year-old-man-his-stomach-moved-and-settled-in-his-chest-for-7-years','2021-01-03 10:28:57','2021-01-03 10:28:57'),(1738,'blogs','content',10,'en','<h1 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 64px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.1; color: #333333; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-weight: bold; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Saving the Life of a 29-year-old Man His Stomach Moved and Settled in his Chest for 7 Years</span></h1>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: #333333; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\">Abdullah, a 29-year-old man, has had a terrible car accident seven years ago, resulted in several injuries in different parts of his body, then he began a long treatment journey and moved between several hospitals where the pain was a companion to him on this journey, he was suffering from acute abdominal pain with recurrent vomiting throughout these seven years.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: #333333; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\">Abdullah recently came to Almoosa Specialist Hospital in Al-Ahsa, where Dr. Mohammed Al-Awadhi, Gastroenterology Consultant performed several tests, which showed a rupture in the left part of the diaphragm with a large opening through which the stomach, spleen and left kidney moved to the chest cavity instead of the abdomen, where they put pressure on the left lung, that resulted in shrinkage, in addition to a strain on the heart and pushed it to the right side.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: #333333; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\">Dr. Ayman Ghoneim, Associate Consultant Cardiothoracic Surgery, who received the patient in the Department of Cardio-Thoracic Surgery, said: &ldquo;We held an urgent meeting that included the General Surgery, Cardiothoracic Surgery departments at Almoosa Specialist Hospital,&nbsp; for coordination to conduct major surgery to restore body organs to normal, putting in mind that the mission will not be easy because the length of time led to adhesions between the abdominal viscera and thoracic organs.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: #333333; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\">Dr. Saeed Abdul-Baqi, general surgery consultant and head of the surgical team who performed this operation said that an opening in the chest was made to remove adhesions between the stomach and the heart membrane, and between the stomach and lung and its pleural membrane, in addition to returning the organs to the normal position in the abdominal cavity and repair of the diaphragm rupture.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: #333333; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\">The surgery took almost 3 hours, and it was successful thanks be to Allah. The operation performed through one incision in the chest. After that Abdullah&rsquo;s condition has improved, then he left the hospital seven days later.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out 0s; color: #333333; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\">Dr. Abdul Baqi concluded that the dangers of such rare cases lie in the ease of injury to the lung, heart or stomach itself, which may lead to bleeding inside the heart or bowel obstruction, which resulted from an injury caused by a car accident seven years ago that&nbsp; not discovered despite his admission to several hospitals during this period, that is one of the rarest cases in the world where most similar cases detected in the first year after the accident, and the world record so far registered one case discovered after five years of the crash.</p>','2021-01-03 10:28:57','2021-01-03 10:28:57'),(1739,'blog_categories','category_name',2,'en','blog category 2','2021-01-03 10:40:20','2021-01-03 10:40:20'),(1740,'doctors','slug',163,'en','dr-shahin-ahmed','2021-01-03 10:40:47','2021-01-03 10:40:47'),(1741,'doctors','name',163,'en','Dr. Shahin Ahmed','2021-01-03 10:40:47','2021-01-03 10:40:47'),(1742,'doctors','title',163,'en','Internal Medicine Consultant ','2021-01-03 10:40:47','2021-01-03 10:40:47'),(1743,'doctors','qualifications',163,'en','speciality: Internal Medicine\nDegree: Doctorate - American Board in Internal Medicine\nAreas of expertise: general internal medicine - treatment and diagnosis of shortness of breath - fatigue - chest pain - severe acute disease cases that affect different organs simultaneously - management of multiple chronic diseases\nLanguages: English\nNationality: Indian\nAge group of patients: adults and children','2021-01-03 10:40:47','2021-01-03 10:40:47'),(1744,'blog_categories','category_name',1,'en','heart','2021-01-03 10:41:13','2021-01-03 10:41:13'),(1745,'blog_categories','category_name',5,'en','Orthopedic & Joints','2021-01-03 10:43:08','2021-01-03 10:43:08'),(1746,'doctors','slug',164,'en','dr-mohammed-al-awadi','2021-01-03 10:43:48','2021-01-03 10:43:48'),(1747,'doctors','name',164,'en','Dr. Mohammed Al-Awadi','2021-01-03 10:43:48','2021-01-03 10:43:48'),(1748,'doctors','title',164,'en','Gastroenterologist','2021-01-03 10:43:48','2021-01-03 10:43:48'),(1749,'doctors','qualifications',164,'en','Specialty: Gastroenterology and Internal Medicine\nDegree: Assistant Professor of Internal Medicine - Doctor of Internal Medicine\nAreas of Expertise: Gastroenterology - Gastrointestinal E